00:12:02,846 --> 00:12:04,307
Is Dr. Breeland around?

252
00:12:04,473 --> 00:12:05,308
He's hunting.

253
00:12:06,850 --> 00:12:09,555
Uh... my mom.

254
00:12:09,589 --> 00:12:11,757
Freaking out.
I told her I moved here.

255
00:12:11,808 --> 00:12:12,857
What's up? You sick?

256
00:12:13,023 --> 00:12:16,478
Oh, I feel as good
as anyone my age would.

257
00:12:16,513 --> 00:12:19,864
But there's been a little
mix-up down at the DMV.

258
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:22,075
Don't suppose you could sign this

259
00:12:22,241 --> 00:12:23,409
for me?

260
00:12:23,575 --> 00:12:26,329
Let me give you an eye test first.

261
00:12:30,860 --> 00:12:33,252
Mom. Uh...
E, F, P,

262
00:12:33,418 --> 00:12:34,462
T, O, Z...

263
00:12:34,628 --> 00:12:36,248
No, you know

264
00:12:36,282 --> 00:12:37,499
what happened with the fellowship.

265
00:12:37,534 --> 00:12:38,841
It's a GP position.

266
00:12:39,007 --> 00:12:39,842
...P, E, C, F...

267
00:12:40,008 --> 00:12:41,969
Alabama, Mom.
The state?

268
00:12:42,135 --> 00:12:44,180
- E...
- No, I'm not having a nervous breakdown,

269
00:12:44,346 --> 00:12:45,874
okay? I...
D, F, C,

270
00:12:45,908 --> 00:12:47,725
- No, it's the TV. Good-bye.
- Z, P.

271
00:12:48,850 --> 00:12:50,796
All right.

272
00:12:53,516 --> 00:12:54,565
Eh...

273
00:12:56,102 --> 00:12:57,777
Thank you very much.

274
00:13:06,660 --> 00:13:08,564
Oh, my latte.

275
00:13:08,598 --> 00:13:11,374
Oh, yeah. Got thirsty
on the way and drank it.

276
00:13:11,540 --> 00:13:12,951
You got a patient.

277
00:13:14,501 --> 00:13:15,503
Oh.

278
00:13:15,669 --> 00:13:18,791
I'm using subcuticular sutures.

279
00:13:18,825 --> 00:13:21,243
So there will barely be a scar.

280
00:13:21,277 --> 00:13:24,762
Well, it's not like I'm gonna
catch a fella now.

281
00:13:24,928 --> 00:13:28,599
Hey, maybe you could give some
dating tips to my daughter here.

282
00:13:28,765 --> 00:13:30,219
You know that thing
about the potato chips,

283
00:13:30,253 --> 00:13:31,269
how you can't eat just one?

284
00:13:31,435 --> 00:13:33,438
Big Mabel feels that way about lunch,

285
00:13:33,604 --> 00:13:35,307
don't ya, honey?

286
00:13:35,341 --> 00:13:39,068
She's always been chubby, but
she's put on a good half ton

287
00:13:39,234 --> 00:13:40,319
since that boyfriend of hers

288
00:13:40,485 --> 00:13:42,697
dumped her.
You'Yo all set.

289
00:13:42,863 --> 00:13:45,032
Use the antibiotic cream twice a day.

290
00:13:45,198 --> 00:13:48,536
Mabel, those dark
patches on your face,

291
00:13:48,702 --> 00:13:50,239
how long have you had those?

292
00:13:50,273 --> 00:13:51,664
I told her to use sunblock.

293
00:13:51,830 --> 00:13:53,499
Come on.

294
00:13:53,665 --> 00:13:57,830
No offense, but we'll be seeing
Dr. Breeland from now on.

295
00:13:57,864 --> 00:13:59,648
You understand.

296
00:14:03,884 --> 00:14:06,538
<i>Clearly, I needed someplace to live.</i>

297
00:14:06,589 --> 00:14:07,847
<i>Mrs. H. arranged for me</i>

298
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:10,475
<i>to stay at the mayor's plantation.</i>

299
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:12,477
<i>I was like, I'm not sleeping</i>

300
00:14:12,643 --> 00:14:14,812
<i>at some old confederate guy's house.</i>

301
00:14:14,978 --> 00:14:17,049
<i>But she said it was either that
or the sidewalk.</i>

302
00:14:17,100 --> 00:14:18,691
<i>So...</i>

303
00:14:22,639 --> 00:14:23,905
No way!

304
00:14:24,071 --> 00:14:25,865
You're the mayor?

305
00:14:26,031 --> 00:14:28,176
Lavon Hayes, the linebacker?

306
00:14:28,194 --> 00:14:30,011
Two Super Bowls, five Pro Bowls.

307
00:14:30,029 --> 00:14:31,287
Four actually.

308
00:14:31,453 --> 00:14:32,955
Well, I rounded up.
You got robbed in '06.

309
00:14:33,121 --> 00:14:35,901
Oh, Lavon Hayes likes your math.

310
00:14:35,952 --> 00:14:37,418
You must be Zoe.

311
00:14:37,584 --> 00:14:39,378
- Yeah.
- Let me show you to your quarters.

312
00:14:39,544 --> 00:14:40,906
All right.

313
00:14:40,957 --> 00:14:42,173
- I got it.
- Are you sure?

314
00:14:42,339 --> 00:14:44,076
Lavon Hayes will get your bags.

315
00:14:44,127 --> 00:14:46,219
Thank you.

316
00:14:46,385 --> 00:14:48,380
You know, you being the mayor here

317
00:14:48,414 --> 00:14:50,699
is the first thing about
BlueBell that I actually like.

318
00:14:50,717 --> 00:14:51,849
Thank you.
How'd that happen?

319
00:14:52,015 --> 00:14:55,420
Well, after ten years in the NFL,

320
00:14:55,769 --> 00:14:58,314
I was a little lost.

321
00:14:58,480 --> 00:15:03,262
So, Lavon Hayes moved back home.

322
00:15:03,313 --> 00:15:05,731
Having played for the Crimson Tide,

323
00:15:05,765 --> 00:15:07,933
I was quite popular around here.

324
00:15:07,984 --> 00:15:10,827
I ran, I won.

325
00:15:12,494 --> 00:15:14,038
Here it is.

326
00:15:15,241 --> 00:15:17,075
Let me get the door for you.

327
00:15:17,110 --> 00:15:18,584
- Watch your step.
- Thanks.

328
00:15:20,460 --> 00:15:22,630
Well, sorry about the
look of the place.

329
00:15:22,796 --> 00:15:27,009
I think you could put your bags
in the back room there.

330
00:15:30,590 --> 00:15:32,932
Huh, it's not my loft in Soho, but

331
00:15:33,098 --> 00:15:35,260
I'll order some stuff
from Barney's online.

332
00:15:35,295 --> 00:15:36,519
Make the place more homey.

333
00:15:36,685 --> 00:15:39,397
You share a generator
with the guy in the gatehouse.

334
00:15:39,682 --> 00:15:42,525
Looks after the place...
Wade Kinsella.

335
00:15:42,691 --> 00:15:46,279
If you've got your curling iron
going while he's got his AC. on,

336
00:15:46,445 --> 00:15:48,406
could be trouble.

337
00:15:50,323 --> 00:15:51,701
Oh, if you do

338
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:55,830
decided to wander, um, keep your
eyes peeled for Burt Reynolds.

339
00:15:57,456 --> 00:15:59,166
All right.

340
00:15:59,332 --> 00:16:00,786
What?

341
00:16:03,128 --> 00:16:05,123
♪ ♪

342
00:16:39,659 --> 00:16:40,833
That sounds good.

343
00:16:40,999 --> 00:16:43,878
I'm crushing the solo, ain't I?

344
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:45,080
Whoo!

345
00:16:46,797 --> 00:16:49,300
- I'm killing it.
- You overheated the generator.

346
00:16:49,466 --> 00:16:51,787
Nice nightgown.

347
00:16:51,821 --> 00:16:53,262
I'm Wade.

348
00:16:53,428 --> 00:16:55,374
Well, that smile might
make all the girls

349
00:16:55,425 --> 00:16:58,184
at the church social swoon, but
it's not going to work on me.

350
00:16:58,350 --> 00:17:02,347
Well, if you're not going
to be polite,

351
00:17:02,382 --> 00:17:04,940
I'm not going to show you
where the fuse box is.

352
00:17:05,106 --> 00:17:07,068
Good night.

353
00:17:07,234 --> 00:17:09,111
All right, Wade.

354
00:17:09,277 --> 00:17:10,522
Keep going, ladies, come on.

355
00:17:10,556 --> 00:17:12,323
I'm just getting warmed up now.

356
00:17:25,210 --> 00:17:28,172
Shh, shh, shh.

357
00:17:28,338 --> 00:17:29,465
George?

358
00:17:29,631 --> 00:17:31,877
- Hey, hey, hey, hey, what?
- Alligator.

359
00:17:31,911 --> 00:17:33,245
- What?
- An alligator!

360
00:17:33,296 --> 00:17:35,497
I'm sorry, I must have got
some mud in my ear.

361
00:17:35,531 --> 00:17:36,999
An alligator.
And alligator?

362
00:17:37,033 --> 00:17:38,933
Why didn't you say so?
That is an emergency.

363
00:17:39,099 --> 00:17:40,935
Just stay, stay back.

364
00:17:44,206 --> 00:17:45,481
Beat it, Burt.

365
00:17:50,277 --> 00:17:53,406
That's Burt Reynolds,
the mayor's pet alligator.

366
00:17:53,572 --> 00:17:56,450
His favorite movie's
<i>Smokey and the Bandit,</i> so...

367
00:17:56,616 --> 00:17:58,386
- That's funny.
- Yeah.

368
00:17:58,404 --> 00:17:59,554
All right.

369
00:17:59,572 --> 00:18:00,788
Oh, come on.

370
00:18:00,954 --> 00:18:02,724
Hey, hey.

371
00:18:02,742 --> 00:18:04,443
I know you're a New Yorker
and everything,

372
00:18:04,494 --> 00:18:07,279
but down here in Alabama, when
somebody interrupts their nightly jog

373
00:18:07,330 --> 00:18:09,414
to climb into the mud
to save our well-toned ass,

374
00:18:09,449 --> 00:18:10,840
we, you know, we say thank you.

375
00:18:11,006 --> 00:18:12,341
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

376
00:18:12,507 --> 00:18:13,592
Oh.

377
00:18:13,758 --> 00:18:15,970
Well, thank you.

378
00:18:17,512 --> 00:18:20,057
I guess I'll be seeing you around.

379
00:18:20,223 --> 00:18:21,576
Yeah.

380
00:18:21,594 --> 00:18:24,603
See? Hey, small towns
have their perks, huh?

381
00:18:28,648 --> 00:18:31,527
<i>BlueBell isn't so horrible, Dad.</i>

382
00:18:31,693 --> 00:18:34,106
The people here aren't so bad.

383
00:18:34,140 --> 00:18:36,358
Maybe I can make a difference.

384
00:18:36,392 --> 00:18:38,593
I have another call.

385
00:18:38,611 --> 00:18:41,480
Call me.
Are you getting my messages?

386
00:18:41,531 --> 00:18:42,898
Bye.

387
00:18:42,932 --> 00:18:44,039
Hello.

388
00:18:44,456 --> 00:18:48,085
Did you sign Old Man Jackson's
eye exam for the DMV today?

389
00:18:48,251 --> 00:18:50,463
Yeah. Why?

390
00:18:50,629 --> 00:18:53,041
'Cause he just ran someone over.

391
00:19:02,333 --> 00:19:03,584
Can't you tell a legally blind man

392
00:19:03,635 --> 00:19:05,311
when he's right in front
of your face?

393
00:19:05,477 --> 00:19:07,354
All you had to do was open his file!

394
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:10,483
Everybody knows Old Man Jackson
memorized the eye chart.

395
00:19:10,649 --> 00:19:12,443
Oh, my God, I feel so bad.
I was distracted.

396
00:19:12,609 --> 00:19:14,695
Well, you should be.

397
00:19:14,861 --> 00:19:16,072
He nearly killed George Tucker.

398
00:19:18,698 --> 00:19:21,076
If you wanted to see me again,
you could have just asked.

399
00:19:21,242 --> 00:19:22,328
It's my shoulder.

400
00:19:22,494 --> 00:19:24,939
Just...
All right.

401
00:19:24,990 --> 00:19:26,207
Ready?

402
00:19:28,041 --> 00:19:29,360
It's dislocated.

403
00:19:29,394 --> 00:19:31,837
It's no big deal. I just
have to put it back into place.

404
00:19:35,882 --> 00:19:36,967
What the hell?!

405
00:19:37,133 --> 00:19:38,402
That's just the morphine.

406
00:19:38,420 --> 00:19:39,970
It's the easy part... baby.

407
00:19:42,507 --> 00:19:43,557
Eventually,

408
00:19:43,723 --> 00:19:44,959
you're going to find out

409
00:19:45,010 --> 00:19:46,510
this whole
getting-run-over-by-a-car thing

410
00:19:46,545 --> 00:19:47,645
was kind of my fault.

411
00:19:47,811 --> 00:19:49,513
Ow! You did it again!

412
00:19:49,548 --> 00:19:51,816
Okay, have you never heard
of bedside manner?

413
00:19:51,982 --> 00:19:53,359
Why is everyone so obsessed
with that?

414
00:19:53,525 --> 00:19:55,820
Because it's nice!

415
00:19:55,986 --> 00:19:57,154
George?

416
00:19:58,273 --> 00:20:01,575
Good. Morphine's working.

417
00:20:02,760 --> 00:20:04,245
OMG, it's true.

418
00:20:04,411 --> 00:20:07,748
Rosie, honey, come on,
it's time for bed.

419
00:20:07,914 --> 00:20:10,167
Aunt Emmeline, this is breaking news.

420
00:20:10,333 --> 00:20:12,486
Rose Hattenbarger,
BlueBell beat blogger

421
00:20:12,537 --> 00:20:14,738
for the otherwise torpid
official town Web site.

422
00:20:14,773 --> 00:20:17,133
So, how does it feel
to be responsible

423
00:20:17,299 --> 00:20:19,885
for maiming George
Tucker, town golden boy?

424
00:20:20,051 --> 00:20:22,054
He is not maimed.

425
00:20:22,220 --> 00:20:25,307
Off the record-- why would
anyone ever leave New York?

426
00:20:25,473 --> 00:20:26,917
New York is everything, and I know.

427
00:20:26,951 --> 00:20:27,977
Read the <i>Daily Intel,</i>

428
00:20:28,143 --> 00:20:30,254
own all the <i>SATC</i> DVDs.

429
00:20:30,288 --> 00:20:31,639
I bet you're a Carrie.

430
00:20:31,673 --> 00:20:33,774
I'm a Charlotte, but
I wish I was a Carrie.

431
00:20:33,940 --> 00:20:37,061
You guys really like
your classic HBO, huh?

432
00:20:37,095 --> 00:20:39,989
But I am a Miranda who also
wishes she was a Carrie.

433
00:20:40,155 --> 00:20:42,324
I knew you and I were
going to be friends.

434
00:20:42,490 --> 00:20:44,827
Well, I guess I could use a friend.

435
00:20:44,993 --> 00:20:47,371
Damn straight.
Brick's here.

436
00:20:51,416 --> 00:20:52,793
Hello, Pickle.

437
00:20:52,959 --> 00:20:54,745
Hi, Brick.

438
00:20:54,779 --> 00:20:57,147
Um, I'll see you later.

439
00:20:57,165 --> 00:20:58,649
We haven't met.

440
00:20:58,667 --> 00:21:00,009
I'm Dr. Zoe Hart.

441
00:21:00,175 --> 00:21:01,785
As far as I'm concerned,

442
00:21:01,819 --> 00:21:03,053
you're just the girl
who almost killed

443
00:21:03,219 --> 00:21:06,390
two people and spoiled
my hunting trip.

444
00:21:06,556 --> 00:21:08,684
How dare you see my patients.

445
00:21:08,850 --> 00:21:12,021
Well, technically, Harley left
his half of the practice to me.

446
00:21:12,187 --> 00:21:14,715
Miss Hart, I'm not going
to share this office...

447
00:21:14,766 --> 00:21:16,191
not for one minute.

448
00:21:16,357 --> 00:21:18,819
I see you have met my lawyer.

449
00:21:18,985 --> 00:21:22,823
When he's conscious, he doesn't lose.

450
00:21:22,989 --> 00:21:25,826
I'm going to be contesting the will.

451
00:21:25,992 --> 00:21:28,120
Harley wasn't in his right mind.

452
00:21:28,286 --> 00:21:29,663
You haven't even given me a chance.

453
00:21:29,829 --> 00:21:31,415
I believe I can do some good here.

454
00:21:31,581 --> 00:21:33,651
Well, bless your heart.

455
00:21:33,685 --> 00:21:36,537
But thingsave been working
just fine here in BlueBell.

456
00:21:36,571 --> 00:21:38,789
We survived Katrina, we survived BP,

457
00:21:38,823 --> 00:21:40,758
by boarding up the windows
and piling up the sandbags

458
00:21:40,924 --> 00:21:43,577
to keep the rot outside

459
00:21:43,628 --> 00:21:45,346
from fouling our community.

460
00:21:45,512 --> 00:21:48,224
And believe you me, Zoe Hart,

461
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:53,729
we are going to chase you away
from our waters.

462
00:21:57,899 --> 00:22:00,060
<i>Well, my night
had quickly gone downhill.</i>

463
00:22:00,095 --> 00:22:02,062
<i>But in times like this,</i>

464
00:22:02,097 --> 00:22:04,406
<i>I find one thing
really helps me through.</i>

465
00:22:04,572 --> 00:22:09,703
Wine! Tell me you have
a nice dry chardonnay.

466
00:22:09,869 --> 00:22:11,455
Yup. Come on.

467
00:22:11,621 --> 00:22:14,692
You're Mabel, right?

468
00:22:14,726 --> 00:22:16,910
Bad day?

469
00:22:16,945 --> 00:22:18,629
You have no idea.

470
00:22:18,795 --> 00:22:20,114
Ugh. Oh, yes, I do.

471
00:22:20,165 --> 00:22:21,590
You met my mama?

472
00:22:21,756 --> 00:22:23,200
Oh, yeah.

473
00:22:23,234 --> 00:22:25,803
Yeah, my mom isn't
exactly supportive, either.

474
00:22:27,178 --> 00:22:30,374
Mabel, I know
it's none of my business,

475
00:22:30,408 --> 00:22:32,743
but the dark patches
on your forehead and face...

476
00:22:32,761 --> 00:22:34,228
you have melasma.

477
00:22:34,394 --> 00:22:35,679
You know you're pregnant, right?

478
00:22:35,714 --> 00:22:37,097
I don't know that.

479
00:22:37,132 --> 00:22:39,082
I haven't taken a test.

480
00:22:39,100 --> 00:22:41,084
Well, I'm sure you can get one here

481
00:22:41,102 --> 00:22:43,237
over by the Slim Jims and duck calls.

482
00:22:44,863 --> 00:22:46,532
Long day.

483
00:22:48,643 --> 00:22:50,611
I didn't think...

484
00:22:50,645 --> 00:22:52,371
We only had sex once.

485
00:22:52,537 --> 00:22:55,290
He told me

486
00:22:55,456 --> 00:22:58,202
he wouldn't do it
if he had to wear a condom.

487
00:22:59,771 --> 00:23:02,939
I didn't want to lose him,
but he left anyway.

488
00:23:02,957 --> 00:23:04,967
So, my mother's right.
I'm stupid.

489
00:23:06,077 --> 00:23:08,328
Look, you need a doctor.

490
00:23:08,380 --> 00:23:10,389
Here. Take this.

491
00:23:10,555 --> 00:23:11,782
Can I have this?

492
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:13,333
I'm gonna give you my number,

493
00:23:13,385 --> 00:23:17,554
and you can call me,
and I won't tell anybody, okay?

494
00:23:17,589 --> 00:23:19,982
Okay, I'll take that.
Hmm.

495
00:23:20,148 --> 00:23:21,842
Thank you.
Owe you some money.

496
00:23:21,893 --> 00:23:24,737
Do you realize that my
engagement party is tomorrow?!

497
00:23:24,903 --> 00:23:26,447
Huh? I mean, what
am I supposed to do?

498
00:23:26,613 --> 00:23:27,865
The photographs!
The press!

499
00:23:28,031 --> 00:23:29,800
The whole thing's
just gonna be ruined!

500
00:23:29,818 --> 00:23:31,285
Seriously, Lemon,
what are you blabbering about?

501
00:23:31,451 --> 00:23:34,413
Well, thanks to you,
my fiancé was in a car accident.

502
00:23:34,579 --> 00:23:36,156
You're engaged to Old Man Jackson?

503
00:23:36,191 --> 00:23:37,833
No, you twit.

504
00:23:37,999 --> 00:23:41,045
I'm engaged to George Tucker.

505
00:23:45,216 --> 00:23:46,800
<i>Clearly, BlueBell
wasn't the answer.</i>

506
00:23:46,966 --> 00:23:49,928
<i>I'd messed up as a doctor</i>

507
00:23:50,094 --> 00:23:52,539
<i>and gotten the guy
I kind of liked run over.</i>

508
00:23:52,590 --> 00:23:55,843
