00:36:45,963 --> 00:36:47,097
But I mean, come on.

775
00:36:47,131 --> 00:36:48,498
BlueBell?

776
00:36:48,664 --> 00:36:50,434
I don't fit in here.

777
00:36:50,468 --> 00:36:52,436
Everybody hates me.

778
00:36:52,470 --> 00:36:54,420
Plus the humidity is
really ruining my hair.

779
00:36:57,475 --> 00:36:59,943
I'm not a family doctor.

780
00:36:59,977 --> 00:37:01,553
I'm gonna be
a cardio-thoracic surgeon.

781
00:37:01,719 --> 00:37:03,972
I've known since I was nine.

782
00:37:04,138 --> 00:37:06,933
I just have to figure out
another way.

783
00:37:09,487 --> 00:37:12,823
You asked me before why Harley
left you his practice.

784
00:37:14,992 --> 00:37:16,526
I didn't tell you the whole truth.

785
00:37:16,692 --> 00:37:18,736
I didn't think it
was my place. But...

786
00:37:18,902 --> 00:37:22,299
I've been carrying this
around since, uh...

787
00:37:22,333 --> 00:37:24,334
since you got here.

788
00:37:26,704 --> 00:37:30,140
Didn't know if I should
give it to you, but...

789
00:37:30,174 --> 00:37:31,749
Here.

790
00:37:34,460 --> 00:37:36,897
That's my mom.

791
00:37:36,931 --> 00:37:37,922
And...

792
00:37:38,088 --> 00:37:40,550
Harley?

793
00:37:40,716 --> 00:37:43,153
Yeah, Zoe.

794
00:37:43,187 --> 00:37:46,306
Harley Wilkes was your father.

795
00:37:48,442 --> 00:37:50,602
Wha...?

796
00:37:52,446 --> 00:37:54,698
You're here! Great!

797
00:37:54,732 --> 00:37:57,584
There's a superb Sancerre
chilling in the car.

798
00:37:57,618 --> 00:38:00,086
We need to talk.

799
00:38:00,121 --> 00:38:03,423
Oh, my...
Oh my God.

800
00:38:03,457 --> 00:38:04,741
Zoe, I can explain.

801
00:38:04,907 --> 00:38:06,426
What's there to explain?

802
00:38:06,460 --> 00:38:08,620
That my entire life has been a lie?

803
00:38:08,786 --> 00:38:11,831
This is the answer to
everything, isn't it?

804
00:38:11,997 --> 00:38:13,934
Why Harley left me the practice,

805
00:38:13,968 --> 00:38:15,376
why Dad stopped loving me?

806
00:38:17,503 --> 00:38:20,273
Because I wasn't his to love.

807
00:38:20,308 --> 00:38:22,383
He knew, didn't he?

808
00:38:24,812 --> 00:38:27,447
When you were ten,
you fell off the swings,

809
00:38:27,481 --> 00:38:29,849
they thought you would
need a transfusion.

810
00:38:30,015 --> 00:38:31,985
But when he donated blood...

811
00:38:34,520 --> 00:38:36,773
He tried to stay in your life,

812
00:38:36,791 --> 00:38:38,107
but I guess it was too hard.

813
00:38:38,273 --> 00:38:39,943
That's why he left?

814
00:38:41,629 --> 00:38:42,487
And what about Harley?

815
00:38:42,653 --> 00:38:44,798
Why not tell me about him?

816
00:38:44,832 --> 00:38:46,658
Was he a psycho?
A pedophile? What?

817
00:38:46,824 --> 00:38:48,752
He was a mistake.

818
00:38:48,786 --> 00:38:50,587
I met him on a cruise.

819
00:38:50,621 --> 00:38:51,838
It was Greece.

820
00:38:51,889 --> 00:38:53,423
He was handsome, older, a gentleman.

821
00:38:53,457 --> 00:38:54,666
It was a fantasy.

822
00:38:54,832 --> 00:38:56,593
But I was engaged.

823
00:38:56,627 --> 00:38:59,262
To someone real.

824
00:38:59,296 --> 00:39:01,431
Did you love him?

825
00:39:01,465 --> 00:39:03,934
It doesn't matter.

826
00:39:03,968 --> 00:39:07,512
I did not belong with him,
just as my child

827
00:39:07,678 --> 00:39:11,107
does not belong in a place like this.

828
00:39:11,141 --> 00:39:13,184
I gave you a father
who was from our world.

829
00:39:13,350 --> 00:39:15,779
I protected you.

830
00:39:15,813 --> 00:39:17,355
That should've been my choice.

831
00:39:17,521 --> 00:39:20,525
I am sorry, Zoe, okay?

832
00:39:20,691 --> 00:39:23,453
I am truly, deeply sorry.

833
00:39:23,487 --> 00:39:26,489
But, please, can we just go home

834
00:39:26,507 --> 00:39:28,491
and discuss this in therapy
like normal people?

835
00:39:28,657 --> 00:39:30,618
You go.

836
00:39:33,163 --> 00:39:35,540
I'm staying here.

837
00:39:43,005 --> 00:39:44,590
<i>Growing up, I was told</i>

838
00:39:44,756 --> 00:39:47,051
<i>that to be a surgeon,
I couldn't let myself feel.</i>

839
00:39:47,217 --> 00:39:49,804
<i>But then, I came to BlueBell.</i>

840
00:39:49,970 --> 00:39:52,682
All the food here is fried.

841
00:39:54,184 --> 00:39:57,153
The whole town smells like mold.

842
00:39:57,187 --> 00:40:00,398
And clearly, the sex
education system is lacking.

843
00:40:01,859 --> 00:40:05,111
They could use a good doctor.

844
00:40:05,277 --> 00:40:08,239
One who cares about her patients.

845
00:40:08,405 --> 00:40:10,967
Maybe, even though you're gone,

846
00:40:11,002 --> 00:40:12,852
there are still some things
you can teach me.

847
00:40:19,708 --> 00:40:24,514
No one ever believed
in me like you did.

848
00:40:24,548 --> 00:40:28,184
You kept sending me
those postcards...

849
00:40:28,218 --> 00:40:29,927
knowing one day I'd be lost.

850
00:40:30,093 --> 00:40:35,859
And maybe following in your...

851
00:40:37,561 --> 00:40:38,770
my real father...

852
00:40:38,936 --> 00:40:43,033
your footsteps for a while, um,

853
00:40:43,067 --> 00:40:46,786
I might find my way.

854
00:40:51,740 --> 00:40:54,711
Thanks.

855
00:41:01,166 --> 00:41:03,136
♪ ♪

856
00:41:18,703 --> 00:41:20,394
Hi.

857
00:41:20,560 --> 00:41:22,772
Zoe, where are you?

858
00:41:22,790 --> 00:41:24,240
I got the Tark Twins here again.

859
00:41:24,274 --> 00:41:25,775
Let me guess.
They were wrestling

860
00:41:25,941 --> 00:41:27,276
in poison oak?

861
00:41:27,442 --> 00:41:28,361
You got it.

862
00:41:28,527 --> 00:41:30,321
I'll be right there.

863
00:41:30,487 --> 00:41:32,198
See you soon, Dr. Hart.

